@prefix bao:  <https://w3id.org/boolean-algebra-ontology#>.
@prefix rdf:  <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>.
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>.
@prefix sh:   <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>.
@prefix :   <http://www.example.org#>.


# The first triple below asserts that the statement "Bill is a horse" is false, while the second triple asserts that the statement "Bill is a horse is false" is itself false.
# By applying the double negation rule to the second triple, the reasoner infers "<<:Bill rdf:type :Horse>> rdf:type bao:True."; that is, the statement "Bill is a horse" is true.
# Together with the first triple, this leads to a contradiction in the knowledge graph.

<<:Bill rdf:type :Horse>> rdf:type bao:False.
<< <<:Bill rdf:type :Horse>> rdf:type bao:False>> rdf:type bao:False.


# Similarly, the first triple below asserts that the statement "Bill is married to Mary" is false, while the second triple asserts that Bill is married to Mary.
# By applying double negation, the reasoner infers that the statement "Bill is married to Mary" is true, leading once again to a contradiction in the knowledge graph.

<< <<:Bill :hasWife :Mary>> rdf:type bao:True>> rdf:type bao:False.
:Bill :hasWife :Mary.